Third-party data
----------------

The bundled word-frequency dictionaries
(all files under app/src/main/assets/dictionaries/) are derived from:

  FrequencyWords by Hermit Dave
  https://github.com/hermitdave/FrequencyWords

  Generated from the OpenSubtitles 2018 corpus
  (https://opus.nlpl.eu/OpenSubtitles.php).

  Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0
  (CC BY-SA 4.0): https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Modifications made for RimBoard: filtered to the alphabetic words of each
language, deduplicated, and truncated by frequency rank to at most —

  200,000 entries for en, tr, de, es, fr, it, pt and ru
  100,000 entries for cs, da, el, fi, hr, hu, id, nl, no, pl, ro, sk, sv
  and uk

Romanian additionally has the legacy cedilla letters (s-cedilla U+015F,
t-cedilla U+0163) folded to the comma-below letters Romanian actually
uses (U+0219, U+021B), with the frequencies of the two spellings summed.
The corpus mixes both; only the comma-below pair is standard. This
leaves that list below the figure above.

The filtering, folding and truncation are done by
tools/fetch_dictionaries.py, which is the authoritative description of
what was changed.

Under the CC BY-SA 4.0 terms, these dictionary files (and any derivative
dictionary files) remain licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0.


